Esther Summerson is the narrator and protagonist. Esther, an orphan, becomes the housekeeper at Bleak House when she, Ada, and Richard are taken in by Mr. Jarndyce. Everyone loves Esther, who is selfless and nurturing, and she becomes the confidante of several young women. Although she eventually does find her mother, circumstances prevent them from developing a relationship. At first a hesitant, insecure narrator, Estherâ€™s confidence in her storytelling grows, and she controls the narrative skillfully.Read anin-depth analysis of Esther Summerson.